post_text:
Dear MCRD Friends and Family,

The Recreation Department is moving ahead with fall sports.

Registration for Tackle football, Flag football Cheerleading, and Soccer all begins today and runs to August 28th.

In regards to Tackle Football there are 2 changes..1. The registration fee is $50.00 but this year pants will be provided. 2. We will be playing other agencies in the area so we will be traveling some. This will mean that games will be on Saturday morning.

We want to elevate our level of play and playing other agencies will do that.

Forms are at the Recreation Department and can also be found on the County website at:

http://www.mitchellcountyga.net/recreation.html

We are really looking forward to the upcoming season and can't wait to get the kids back playing.

Sincerely,

Mitchell County Recreation Department

You can also view the meetings on Facebook Live.

post_text:
April 28,2020

PUBLIC NOTICE FOR DEBRIS REMOVAL

Mitchell County has received approval from the Georgia Environmental Protection Division to collect vegetative storm debris from the unincorporated area directly impacted by the recent tornado. Vegetative storm debris includes only limbs, stumps, branches, yard waste and trees and must be placed near the road but should not be placed in the ditches. Mitchell County will not be responsible for removing debris that contains any materials other than those defined as vegetative storm debris or debris that has been placed by a contractor. Contractors may contact Mitchell County at 229-336-6200. This service will be made available through May 29, 2020.
